>[Question]
>I have done all the problems except one that I am having a hard time 
>solving.
>
>   4+2/x  divided by  x/4 + 1/8 
> 
>  I am assuming the LCD is 8x, and I believe the correct answer is 
>16/x but I need help.  at the end I come up with 48/3x which reduces 
>to 16/x. But i'm not sure if this is correct.  Thanks for your help, 
>Scott
>
>[Difficulty]
>multiplying lcd into the fractions.
>
>[Thoughts]
>with LCD 8x  4+2/x = 4+16  and x/4+1/8 = 2x^2+ x  
>I don't think this is correct and need help.   

Thanks for writing to Ask Dr. Math, Scott!

8*x*(4 + 2/x) = 32*x + 16, and not 4 + 16.
8*x*(x/4 + 1/8) = 2*x^2 + x.

Now factor both numerator and denominator, and cancel the common
factor of 2*x + 1.

Feel free to reply if I can help further with this question.


